FG-321 — Accessibility Pack (PDF/UA • Alt-Text • Tagging)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Make your PDFs readable by everyone—and harder to reject.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Export PDF/UA; use proper H1/H2 tags; add alt-text to figures (what the chart proves); ensure reading order; set Title metadata; run an accessibility checker log and attach as Ex. A if policy allows.
	•	📝 Assignment: Re-export one filing with PDF/UA, heading tags, and alt-text; save the checker log.
	•	✅ Model Response: “PDF/UA ✓; H1/H2 ✓; alt-text added (‘red band = harm window’); Title set ‘Opening Brief v3’.“
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Accessible = professional = harder to ignore.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A PDF tile with badges: PDF/UA • Alt-text • Tags.

⸻

FG-322 — Micro-Extension Motion (Good Cause • Diligence • No Prejudice)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Extensions win on math + diligence, not drama.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Four sentences: ask (+ days/date); good-cause fact (with pin); diligence steps; no prejudice line. Add a tiny schedule card rolled for weekends.
	•	📝 Assignment: Rewrite your extension into ≤90 words with one date pin.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Extend 7 days to 09/14; transcript denied 09/01 (Clerk note Ex A). Diligence shown; opposing neutral; no schedule impact.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Small + dated + diligent = yes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A date chip “+7” beside a tidy clock table.

⸻

FG-323 — Motions Panel Pack (Short • Neutral • Signable)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Motions units decide off short, neutral papers.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One page: ask; standard (one cite); two pins; two-line order; scope/sunset/status line. Hash; file fast.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a motions template you can fill in 5 minutes.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Relief: admin stay ¶3 72h; abuse—wrong test (cite); pins Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2; status 48h; sunset auto.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Motions love small targets.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A one-page card with four slim blocks and a checkbox order.

⸻

FG-324 — TOC Answer Lines (Headings that Decide)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Your TOC should read like a win card.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Convert headings to answers (≤12 words), mirror bookmarks, and remove filler subheads. Keep TOC + bookmarks identical.
	•	📝 Assignment: Rewrite three TOC lines to answer the issue.
	•	✅ Model Response: “I. Court erred by skipping harm findings. II. Error prejudiced outcome.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: An answer-TOC guides skim-judging.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A TOC with bold, answer-like lines.

⸻

FG-325 — Greyscale & Pattern Fallback (When Color Conveys Meaning)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Preserve meaning when prints lose color.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Add a greyscale key (shapes/patterns); label figure regions (“red band = ¶3 window” → “hatched band”); alt-text mirrors the key; cite exact region pin.
	•	📝 Assignment: Produce a greyscale version of one figure with a legend.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Tab D at 2 (hatched band = ¶3 window); alt-text: ‘Hatched band shows 7/21–8/02 gap.’”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Meaning should survive the printer.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Side-by-side color vs greyscale with a small pattern legend.

⸻

FG-326 — Posture Slip (Triangle Card You Paste Everywhere)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Keep Statute • Clock • Copies visible on every draft.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One slip line: “§1291/§1292; Rule 58 08/15 → NOA 08/19; Tabs 1–2”; paste on page one, OA card, and appendix guide; delete if redundant in final.
	•	📝 Assignment: Print and paste your posture slip in three places.
	•	✅ Model Response: “§1291; Rule 58 on 08/15; NOA 08/19; judgment/PI at Tabs 1–2.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Orientation removes resistance.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A little triangle sticker at the bottom of the first page.

⸻

FG-327 — 28(i) Duplication Certification (One Voice, Many Parties)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Tell the court who speaks on what—and who adopts.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: File a duplication certification: owner per issue; adopters under FRAP 28(i); shared pin atlas; page/word caps affirmed.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line 28(i) notice with an owner/adopter grid.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Issue 1—Appellant; Issue 2—Cross-Appellant; others adopt §II.A; shared atlas v1.2; caps O/R/Rep: 6k/6k/3k.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One map, no echoes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small matrix “Owner / Adopter / Pins.”

⸻

FG-328 — OA Demonstrative Ask (Policy-Clean & Narrow)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Ask to use one demonstrative tied to one page.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Identify policy cite; label neutral (“Demonstrative A”); 3 photos with scale; view copy (2–3 pp) with callouts; one-line order; return/lodge plan.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line OA demonstrative request with a return clause.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Permit Demonstrative A (scale model) for 2 min; auth photos Ex A; view copy Tab 6; return upon disposition.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Narrow + documented = granted.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A neutral model photo with a tiny “2 min” tag.

⸻

FG-329 — Formatting Compliance Certificate (Fonts • Margins • Spacing)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Certify format so intake can’t stall you.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One paragraph: font (14-pt), spacing, margins, binding if required; cite local rule; match Title metadata; attach a one-page checklist.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add a formatting certificate to your templates.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Complies with LR 32: 14-pt font, double-spaced, margins 1”, Title set; checklist attached.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Format fuel removes clerical friction.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ruler icon over a page with margin guides.

⸻

FG-330 — Email-to-Docket Conversion Macro (Short Notice, One Ask)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Important emails must be converted to the record.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Notice headings: Date/Time • Participants • Summary • Pin to policy; attach the thread as exhibit; one-line ask (set date/confirm scope).
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 7-line “Notice of Clerk Communication” macro and test it on a real email.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Clerk email 08/19 14:03—docket delay; policy cite; Ex A thread; ask: confirm filing date/time.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Inboxes fade; dockets last.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: An envelope arrowing into a “FILED” stamp